  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"single-post\"\u003e\n        \n                \n        \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"750\" height=\"702\" src=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-750x702.png\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-750x702.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-1090x1020.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-210x197.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-768x719.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts.png 1154w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-attachment-id=\"77694\" data-permalink=\"https://flowingdata.com/2025/02/25/estimating-the-laziness-of-federal-workers/federal-worker-efforts/\" data-orig-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts.png\" data-orig-size=\"1154,1080\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"federal worker efforts\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-750x702.png\" data-large-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/federal-worker-efforts-1090x1020.png\"/\u003e                    \u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                    \n                \u003cp\u003eSome might have you believe that federal employees don’t put in the work. For the Washington Post’s Department of Data, Andrew Van Dam shows \u003ca href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2025/02/21/are-federal-workers-lazy-lets-look-data/?pwapi_token=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..jzbHTwXz4lozGacBJlysQK_yvnq2nIQjIM_V5dH1euk\"\u003edata that suggests otherwise\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn case you’re unfamiliar with the WP column, Van Dam (usually) attempts to answer a question each week using data. I like how he takes the reader through the exploratory process of trying to figure things out. Most of the time, you can’t answer data questions directly, because there isn’t a direct metric for say, worker efforts. So you analyze the data that is available, build related insights, and see if that gets you to where you need to go.  \u003c/p\u003e\n                \n                \n                                        \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n                    \n        \n\t\t\n                \n        \n                        \t\t\n\n        \n        \n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
